name: The Dream that the Princess Saw

description:
Japanese title: Tasogare (黄昏)

Leaf ninja, she notifies the others and the Hebi members quickly leave the inn. To allow Sasuke to focus on his coming battle with Itachi, Karin comes up with a plan to keep the Leaf ninja occupied.
name: Twilight

description:
Japanese title: Dokonjō ninden ~Jiraiya ninpōchō~ Zenpen (ド根性忍伝～自来也忍法帖～前編)

During the reign of the Second Hokage, the young Jiraiya, Orochimaru, and Tsunade are assigned to Hiruzen Sarutobi’s platoon as Genins.
name: Tales of a Gutsy Ninja: Jiraiya Ninja Scrolls, Part 1

description:
Japanese title: Dokonjō ninden ~Jiraiya ninpōchō~ Kōhen (ド根性忍伝～自来也忍法帖～後編)

Jiraiya’s journey to seek out a student is postponed due to the outbreak of the Third Great Ninja War. Jiraiya joins Tsunade and Orochimaru to battle the Village Hidden in the Rain.
name: Tales of a Gutsy Ninja – Jiraiya Ninja Scrolls, Part 2

description:
Japanese title: Sennyū! Amegakure no Sato (潜入! 雨隠れの里)

Jiraiya successfully infiltrates the Hidden Rain Village by hiding inside the toad Gamagoro. He sets out to gather information but finds no indications of a civil war occurring within the village.
name: Infiltrate! the Village Hidden in the Rain

description:
Japanese title: Kami to natta Otoko (神となった男)

Foreseeing a possible battle, Jiraiya takes precautionary measures by storage releasing the scroll toad that commands the key to Naruto’s Eight-Signed Seal.
name: The Man Who Became God

description:
Japanese title: Hatsudō! Sennin Mōdo (発動! 仙人モード)

Jiraiya battles to defeat his former student Pain, who is now driven by his twisted ideals as an Akatsuki member.
name: Honored Sage Mode!

description:
Japanese title: Pein Rikudō, kenzan (ペイン六道、見参)

Jiraiya completes his Sage Mode transformation to battle the three Pains.
name: In Attendance, the Six Paths of Pain

description:
Japanese title: Jiraiya gōketsu monogatari (自来也豪傑物語)

Having lost his arm, Jiraiya is outmatched by the six Pains now appearing before him. Of the six, the one called Tendo is revealed to be Jiraiya’s former student Yahiko.
name: The Tale of Jiraiya the Gallant

description:
Japanese title: Utage e no izanai (宴への誘い)

Sasuke arrives at one of the Akatsuki hideouts, having followed in Itachi’s footsteps. When Sasuke is about to enter the hideout alone, his older brother Itachi finally appears before him…
name: Banquet Invitation

description:
Japanese title: Nagaki toki no naka de... (長き瞬間の中で...)

While Itachi waits for Sasuke in the Uchiha hideout, he recalls the past incident that led to his defection from the Leaf Village.
name: The Longest Moment

description:
Japanese title: Mangekyō Sharingan no hikari to yami (万華鏡写輪眼の光と闇)

Following their fierce genjutsu battle with the Sharingan, Itachi explains the secret behind the most powerful ocular jutsu, the Mangekyo Sharingan, and the history of the Uchiha clan…
name: The Light & Dark of the Mangekyo Sharingan

description:
Japanese title: Amaterasu (天照)

Sasuke loses his left eye to Itachi, but it turns out to be a genjutsu created by the Mangekyo Sharingan. Breaking free of the Tsukuyomi by force, Sasuke makes a furious comeback against the injured Itachi.
name: Amaterasu!

description:
Japanese title: Shūen (終焉)

At the climax of the battle, both Itachi and Sasuke run out of chakra. However, Sasuke reveals that his actions up until now were only a preparation for his final jutsu.
name: The End

description:
Japanese title: Tobi no nazo (トビの謎)

Naruto and his comrades find themselves held up by Tobi, whose strange jutsu is more than just a simple genjutsu.
name: The Mystery of Tobi

description:
Japanese title: Innen (因縁)

In the Akatsuki hideout Sasuke comes face to face with Madara. Announcing himself as Itachi’s accomplice from that fateful night, Madara goes on to tell Sasuke the truth about Itachi that he could never have known.
name: Fate

description:
Japanese title: Shinjitsu (真実)

The Uchiha clan was plotting a coup d’etat. The story as told by Madara leaves Sasuke at a loss for words. Because of his gifted talent, Itachi was forced to suffer, torn between his loyalties to the Leaf Village and the Uchiha clan.
name: Truth

description:
Japanese title: Unraikyō no tatakai (雲雷峡の闘い)

Flame from the Amaterasu still remains on the battlefield as Naruto and his teammates continue to search for Sasuke. But despite the search team’s best efforts, they cannot find any trace of him.
name: Battle of Unraikyo

deck: Caitlin brings Barry out to a karaoke bar, hoping they both meet someone new; Cisco thinks about Hartley's dangerous proposition; Henry's snooping gets him into trouble.
description: LOVE IS IN THE AIR — Caitlin (Danielle Panabaker) decides that she and Barry (Grant Gustin) need to move on from Ronnie (guest star Robbie Amell) and Iris (Candice Patton) and find new loves so she takes him for a night out at the local karaoke bar. Caitlin doesn’t have any luck making a love connection but Barry meets Linda Park (guest star Malese Jow), a sports reporter for the Central City Picture News, and asks her out on a date. When Barry tells Iris he has a date, Iris is surprised by her reaction. Meanwhile, Cisco (Carlos Ramon) considers Hartley’s (guest star Andy Mientus) dangerous offer and the team searches for Shawna (guest star Britne Oldford), a meta-human with teleportation powers, who just busted her boyfriend Clay (guest star Micah Parker) out of Iron Heights. When Henry (guest star John Wesley Shipps) snoops around in an attempt to help Joe (Jesse L. Martin) and Barry solve the crime, he ends up in the infirmary after getting roughed up by inmates. Rob Hardy directed the episode written by Aaron Helbing & Todd Helbing
name: Crazy For You

description:
Japanese title: Hachibi' tai 'Sasuke' (「八尾」対「サスケ」)

The Taka split up with the Akatsuki to hunt down the remaining Tailed Beast. At the Land of Lightning they go up against Killer Bee, whose attack utilizing Lightning Style and seven blades proves to be more than a match for them.
name: The Eight-Tails vs. Sasuke

description:
Japanese title: Fūraibō (風来坊)

The Leaf ninja fail to capture Itachi and also lose track of Sasuke. Calling off their pursuit, the team is heading back to the village when an urgent assignment from Lady Tsunade arrives.
name: Wanderer

description:
Japanese title: Kinjutsu no keishōsha (禁術の継承者)

Naruto and his teammates are assigned to escort Hotaru, En no Gyoja’s granddaughter, to the Tsuchigumo Clan’s village located in the mountains. But Hotaru’s mind is still attached to Utakata, who left after Naruto’s arrival…
name: Successor of the Forbidden Jutsu

description:
Japanese title: Keishōsha no omoi (継承者の想い)

Having arrived at the village, Hotaru parts with Naruto and his team. But the Magaki Troops are one step ahead and threaten Hotaru to hand over the forbidden jutsu.
name: The Successor's Wish

description:
Japanese title: Nukenin no kako (抜け忍の過去)

Yamato and Sai recognize their opponents as trackers from the Hidden Mist Village, but Naruto attacks without questioning. The Hidden Mist demands Utakata be handed over to them in exchange for Hotaru.
name: Rogue Ninja’s Past

description:
Japanese title: Yami no kōkeisha (闇の後継者)

Hotaru is brought back to the fort in Mount Katsuragi. Naruto, outraged to learn the forbidden jutsu was embedded inside Hotaru, demands an explanation from Tonbei. But it was none other than Hotaru herself who wished for this.
name: Heir to Darkness

description:
Japanese title: Betsuri (別離)

Believing Shiranami’s story, Hotaru writes a parting letter addressed to Utakata and leaves Mount Katsuragi. Meanwhile Naruto, still searching for Shiranami, falls into the Magaki Troops’ trap but manages to escape thanks to help from Utakata.
name: Separation

description:
Japanese title: Kinjutsu hatsudō (禁術発動)

Naruto and Utakata successfully enter the Tsuchigumo village thanks to help from Sakura, Sai, and Yamato. Utakata senses the chakra filling the atmosphere and terrain behaving oddly.
name: The Forbidden Jutsu Released

description:
Japanese title: Shitei (師弟)

Hotaru, under the control of Shiranami’s jutsu, uses the Forbidden Jutsu against Naruto and Utakata. Shiranami trembles with joy, having witnessed the power of the Forbidden Jutsu, while Hotaru is consumed by deep despair.
name: Master and Student

description:
Japanese title: Hihō (悲報)

Returning from the mission, Naruto recollects his strange encounter with Itachi. What did the now deceased Itachi wish to tell him? As Naruto ponders this, Kakashi makes an abrupt visit.
name: Somber News

first_appearance_objects.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

object_credits.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

description:
Japanese title: Shi no Kage o Otte (師の影を追って)

Naruto wanders the streets of the Leaf Village, grief stricken over the death of Jiraiya. Unable to overcome his feeling of loss, Naruto traces back through his memories of Jiraiya. What can help the heartbroken Naruto get back on his feet?
name: Following the Master's Shadow

description:
Japanese title: Angō Kaidoku (暗号解読)

Naruto and his friends successfully decipher the code Jiraiya left behind with the help of some information Naruto has.
name: Decryption

description:
Japanese title: Daiichi no Kadai (第一の課題)

At Mount Myoboku, Naruto begins his Sage Jutsu training under Fukasaku. The first challenge is “Don’t move.” Fukasaku explains that an extensive amount of time is necessary in order to take in nature energy.
name: The First Challenge

first_appearance_objects.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

object_credits.name: Demonic Statue of the Outer Path

description:
Japanese title: Shi o Koeru Toki (師を超えるとき)

Naruto continues his Sage training at Mount Myoboku, but with very slow progress. Fukasaku runs out of patience and suggests they move on to the next training…
name: Surpassing the Master

description:
Japanese title: Konoha Shūgeki! (木ノ葉襲撃!)

Shikamaru and the others wait for the information Jiraiya brought back to be analyzed. The Hidden Leaf ninja continue their data analysis, when disaster strikes the village.
name: Assault on the Leaf Village

description:
Japanese title: Shinjiru Chikara (信じる力)

The Leaf Village is under heavy attack from Pain and Konan. Hearing the Akatsuki attack, Tsunade attempts to contact Fukasaku…
name: Power to Believe

description:
Japanese title: Pein vs Kakashi (ペインvsカカシ)

In one area of the village, Kakashi enters battle against Tendo Pain, but he can’t keep up with Tendo’s mysterious attacks.
name: Pain Vs. Kakashi

description:
Japanese title: Pein no Nazo (ペインの謎)

The Leaf Village is under heavy attack from the Akatsuki. Underneath the village Danzo takes action to achieve his ambition.
name: Mystery of Pain

description: VERTIGO (GUEST STAR PETER STORMARE) RETURNS AND PITS CANARY AGAINST BLACK CANARY — Oliver (Stephen Amell) is thrown by the changes within Team Arrow. He’s used to calling the shots but sees that the team has evolved in his absence and tensions quickly escalate in the lair. Oliver is furious that Laurel (Katie Cassidy) has been going out as the Black Canary and tells her to stop risking her life, but when Vertigo (guest star Peter Stormare) hits the streets again, Laurel goes against Oliver’s wishes and tracks down Vertigo who hits her with a full dose of the drug. Laurel’s biggest fears revolve around her sister Sara (guest star Caity Lotz) so the Vertigo causes her to hallucinate an epic fight between Canary and Black Canary. Meanwhile, Chase (guest star Austin Butler) surprises Thea (Willa Holland), and Roy (Colton Haynes) warns Thea to stay away from Malcolm (John Barrowman).
name: Canaries

description:
Japanese title: Sei wa Sarutobi, Na wa Konohamaru! (姓は猿飛、名は木ノ葉丸!)

Konohamaru, Moegi, and Udon are shocked to see the disaster that has struck their home village. But to fulfill their duties as genin, each races out to direct the villagers to a safe location.
name: Surname Is Sarutobi! Given Name, Konohamaru!

description:
Japanese title: Sekai ni Itami o (世界に痛みを)

Tsunade comes face to face with Tendo Pain on the rooftop of the Hokage mansion. When Pain demands the Nine Tails be handed over, Tsunade refuses.
name: Pain to the World
